div.div:
PATCH: Remove "messageFrom" from DefaultEmail class
The "messageFrom" attribute and its instances were removed from the DefaultEmail class and the SendEmail screen. This refactors aims to simplify the implementation since the "from" field is not necessary in this context, as it is always the authenticated user sending the email.

PATCH: Refactor 'CreateSendEmail' model and migration
Refactored 'CreateSendEmail' model and its corresponding migration to better reflect their purpose. The fields 'to', 'subject', and 'message' now accurately map to the 'send_email' database table, improving data structuring and access. The migration file was also renamed for consistency.

PATCH: Set database table in CreateSendEmail model
The 'CreateSendEmail' model has been updated, specifying the database table as 'send_email'. This change better defines the relationship of the model to its corresponding database table, ensuring data is properly stored and retrieved.

PATCH: Refactor 'CreateSendEmail' model and update 'SendEmail' method
The 'table' array in the 'CreateSendEmail' model has been replaced with the 'fillable' array. The 'sendEmail' method in the 'SendEmail' screen now has a return type of 'RedirectResponse'. This simplifies the process of storing email composition details and improves the email sending functionality.

PATCH: Add 'send_email' migration and update email sending process
A new database migration for 'send_email' has been added. In addition, the process of sending emails has been updated to proper email model and related library functions in 'SendEmail' screen. Changes include refactoring to use newly created 'CreateSendEmail' model, layout setup for email composition page, and saving email details before sending.
